	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_61485412"><p>SHA256 isn't a block cipher. It's a hash algorithm.  The parent post is correct that Quantum doesn't help SHA256.</p><p>Block ciphers are weakened, but not badly. It effectively halves the keylength.  128 bit is considered *plenty* and 256 bit keys are commonly used.</p><p>Asymmetric algorithms are where the trouble is.  Bitcoin uses ECDSA, so that would be the problem that needs addressing.</p></div>
	</div>

